== About ==

Gridpulse is used by the ARCS National Grid to help monitor the status of grid gateway machines. It reports information via email (note: sending hosts must be in DNS) back to a central server located at. http://status.arcs.org.au/

== Install ==

Gridpulse should be run using a scheduler like cron

Example:
3,23,43 * * * * /usr/local/bin/gridpulse grid_pulse@lists.arcs.org.au >/dev/null 2>&1

